226
00:11:09,820 --> 00:11:11,140
but now suddenly no one's buying.

227
00:11:12,540 --> 00:11:14,180
Is someone targeting LT?

228
00:11:17,060 --> 00:11:18,060
You noticed too.

229
00:11:20,660 --> 00:11:21,300
Wang's?

230
00:11:23,060 --> 00:11:24,180
Why would he come after you?

231
00:11:25,180 --> 00:11:26,660
You've already withdrawn
from Training Box.

232
00:11:30,300 --> 00:11:32,020
He wants something more precious
from me.

233
00:11:33,060 --> 00:11:34,180
Something more precious?

234
00:11:36,860 --> 00:11:37,820
He won't get his way.

235
00:11:40,060 --> 00:11:40,700
That's good.

236
00:11:43,620 --> 00:11:45,700
I'm moving the company out of Shanghai.

237
00:11:47,740 --> 00:11:48,580
Really?

238
00:11:51,860 --> 00:11:52,620
Then, where to?

239
00:11:52,980 --> 00:11:53,500
Putian.

240
00:11:54,420 --> 00:11:55,020
My hometown.

241
00:11:56,300 --> 00:11:57,500
LT's shoe factory is there.

242
00:11:58,500 --> 00:11:59,780
That's where LT started.

243
00:12:01,100 --> 00:12:02,140
When are you moving?

244
00:12:03,500 --> 00:12:05,580
I'll announce the move

245
00:12:06,300 --> 00:12:07,020
today.

246
00:12:08,300 --> 00:12:09,660
But Putian is too far from Shanghai.

247
00:12:10,500 --> 00:12:12,140
Will this spark a mass exodus of staff

248
00:12:12,820 --> 00:12:14,020
and trigger widespread resignations?

249
00:12:16,420 --> 00:12:17,980
This is the most cost-effective solution

250
00:12:19,260 --> 00:12:21,180
I can think of right now.

251
00:12:23,500 --> 00:12:24,900
The production line must keep running
no matter what.

252
00:12:26,900 --> 00:12:27,940
Maybe you should reconsider.

253
00:12:28,660 --> 00:12:30,060
I've reached out to other buyers.

254
00:12:30,380 --> 00:12:31,660
I should hear back soon.

255
00:12:31,900 --> 00:12:32,420
Don't bother.

256
00:12:34,380 --> 00:12:35,980
The funding gap this time is too large.

257
00:12:36,340 --> 00:12:37,900
Regardless of whether we can
sell the materials or not...

258
00:12:39,620 --> 00:12:40,780
we have to move out of Shanghai.

259
00:12:42,340 --> 00:12:43,020
But...

260
00:12:44,620 --> 00:12:45,180
Don't worry.

261
00:12:46,660 --> 00:12:48,380
I believe we'll be back soon.

262
00:12:59,940 --> 00:13:02,580
[LT Capital]

263
00:13:02,580 --> 00:13:03,620
What's going on?

264
00:13:03,820 --> 00:13:05,020
Looks like everyone's here today.

265
00:13:05,500 --> 00:13:06,700
Why did they

266
00:13:06,700 --> 00:13:07,460
suddenly gather everyone here?

267
00:13:07,500 --> 00:13:08,900
No idea. With such a big turnout,

268
00:13:08,980 --> 00:13:10,820
it must be something important.

269
00:13:10,940 --> 00:13:12,340
Obviously.

270
00:13:12,460 --> 00:13:14,020
But what exactly?

271
00:13:14,140 --> 00:13:15,420
Right, what's the important thing?

272
00:13:15,620 --> 00:13:16,300
Exactly.

273
00:13:16,780 --> 00:13:18,380
Are there layoffs coming?

274
00:13:18,540 --> 00:13:19,700
- Layoffs?
- Layoffs?

275
00:13:19,700 --> 00:13:20,580
No way.

276
00:13:20,580 --> 00:13:21,620
Why not?

277
00:13:24,180 --> 00:13:25,100
Everyone, quiet down.

278
00:13:25,780 --> 00:13:26,660
Listen up.

279
00:13:27,140 --> 00:13:28,180
I believe you all know

280
00:13:28,180 --> 00:13:29,700
the situation of the company.

281
00:13:30,580 --> 00:13:31,980
Thanks for your hard work

282
00:13:31,980 --> 00:13:32,900
over the years.

283
00:13:33,780 --> 00:13:34,660
After discussion,

284
00:13:35,260 --> 00:13:37,100
we've decided to move the company
to Putian.

285
00:13:37,900 --> 00:13:39,940
To Putian?

286
00:13:40,460 --> 00:13:41,380
That's so far. It's in Fujian.

287
00:13:41,380 --> 00:13:41,860
Exactly.

288
00:13:43,100 --> 00:13:44,180
That's so far.

289
00:13:44,300 --> 00:13:45,940
Right. Why is it so sudden?

290
00:13:46,460 --> 00:13:47,180
Exactly.

291
00:13:47,300 --> 00:13:49,700
Will we get pay cuts if we move?

292
00:13:49,860 --> 00:13:50,780
Right.

